- A separate git repository from the CMSSW one is used /opt/ppd/scratch/olaiya/repo/git/NTupler.git/.git This is accessed by using rgit instead of git which is alias via the command alias rgit='git --git-dir=/opt/ppd/scratch/olaiya/repo/git/NTupler.git/.git'
- You have to run rgit from inside the NTupler directory
- The code that runs over the data and produces the ntuples is PATNTupler/plugins/MiniAnalyzer.cc which runs over miniAOD files as specified in PATNTupler/plugins/run.py
- PATNTupler/plugins/run.py specifies the miniAOD files to run over. It can be a reduce miniAOD file or the standard miniAOD file. If it is a reducedMiniAOD file it needs to have the following collections:

LHEEventProduct                    "source"                    ""                "LHEFile"   
edm::TriggerResults                "TriggerResults"            ""                "PAT"       
vector<pat::Electron>              "slimmedElectrons"          ""                "PAT"       
vector<pat::Jet>                   "slimmedJets"               ""                "PAT"       
vector<pat::Jet>                   "slimmedJetsAK8"            ""                "PAT"       
vector<pat::MET>                   "slimmedMETs"               ""                "PAT"       
vector<pat::Muon>                  "slimmedMuons"              ""                "PAT"       
vector<reco::GenParticle>          "prunedGenParticles"        ""                "PAT"       
vector<reco::GsfElectronCore>      "reducedEgamma"             "reducedGedGsfElectronCores"   "PAT"       
vector<reco::SuperCluster>         "reducedEgamma"             "reducedSuperClusters"   "PAT"       
vector<reco::Vertex>               "offlineSlimmedPrimaryVertices"   ""                "PAT"       
